The Technical and Vocational Education and Training Authority has launched a crackdown on unregistered colleges in Mombasa.On Tuesday, TVETA officer George Odero and the police stormed Patana College and ordered it closed indefinitely for failing to register with the authority.Administrators were arrested and will be charged with operating an unaccredited institution. They risk a fine of Sh10 million or three years in prison.Odero said the authority has received many complaints from former students unable to find work because their certificates are not recognised by employers.The crackdown is underway countrywide.